    {
      "id": "970ef202437ba35033c5aefdd729d370dd4a6558",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-31 16:23:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThis should also be cherry-picked to master. One question is if thus test number conflicts on master or not?  If it does, I'd prefer to keep the same test numbers on both branches.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "90ec7777ba166eaff6fc18d1500f6feddb3fdc8a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-31 16:27:35.000000000",
      "message": "Change has been successfully cherry-picked as 0391e57426de8cbdc95392c510e201aa8c222fc3.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "e33a1262c1b4dba2aeaa0fda725e8b5e4b2ad280",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-31 16:28:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nthe test numbers do ocnflict so we need a new renumbering patch for master",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "58e5b5a2b9e3447b0c4e67384b39616878c1155c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-31 19:09:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIn that case, it would have been better to not land the b2_1 patch until it got the same test number as master. Otherwise it is too confusing to report bugs in Jira.  I didn't think of this until after I submitted my inspection. \n\nFan Yong, can you please submit a new patch for master, and a patch for b2_1 that makes the test number march that on master.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "5700945bcb7d7b35e8e5b556d29da60c107eddfc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-31 19:31:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nActually I suspect it's better to just submit a patch to master that renames patches on master so that this test is same number aas b2_1 and the reast are renumbered up",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "03e3af45f7bdf65945b7dfe8d5989eb1895039bd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-03 01:46:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe potential problem with renumbering the tests on master is that it will cause any bugs in Jira to reference the wrong test number, and may also cause test number mismatches in b2_2 and b2_3. I think it would be a lot less complex to land the test on master and then fix this one on b2_1 to match.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    }
  ],
